The paper deals with testing properties of Boolean functions, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of sparse GF(2) polynomials suggests connections to algebraic complexity theory and coding theory, which are often studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also involves learning algorithms, which are a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the analysis of how sparse GF(2) polynomials simplify under certain restrictions suggests connections to combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
